{"word":"G3813 - παιδίον - paidíon - pahee-dee'-on - Child","slug":"G3813","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">παιδίον</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>paidíon"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>pahee-dee'-on"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Child"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C0;&#x03B1;&#x03B9;&#x03B4;&#x03B9;&#x0301;&#x03BF;&#x03BD; - paidion</b> - <i>pahee-dee'-on</i><p/>Neuter diminutive of <a href=\"#/G3816\">G3816</a>; a <i>childling</i> (of either sex), that is, (properly) an infant, or (by extension) a half grown <i>boy</i> or girl; figuratively an <i>immature</i> Christian: - (little, young) child, damsel."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G3808\">G3808</a>, <a href=\"#/G3812\">G3812</a>, <a href=\"#/G3814\">G3814</a>, <a href=\"#/G3816\">G3816</a>"}]}